{"word":"G3565 - νύμφη - nýmphē - noom-fay' - Bride","slug":"G3565","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">νύμφη</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nýmphē"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>noom-fay'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bride"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BD;&#x03C5;&#x0301;&#x03BC;&#x03C6;&#x03B7; - numphe&#x0304;</b> - <i>noom-fay'</i><p/>From a primary but obsolete verb <b>&#x03BD;&#x03C5;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03C4;&#x03C9;</b> <b>nupto&#x0304;</b> (to <i>veil</i> as a bride; compare the Latin <i>&ldquo;nupto&rdquo;</i>, to <i>marry</i>); a young <i>married</i> woman (as <i>veiled</i>), including a <i>betrothed</i> girl; by implication, a <i>son's wife:</i> - bride, daughter in law."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3566\">G3566</a>, <a href=\"#/G3567\">G3567</a>"}]}